Products.FullDescription: Amy's Kitchen Gluten Free Rice Mac & Cheese
Products.RichDescription: At Amy's we do not believe that ?free from gluten? means ?free from flavour?, so our chefs created a gluten free version just as tasty as the original. First they make a roux by browning gluten free rice flour in creamy butter and then add milk, stirring carefully till the sauce is just the right consistency. After that, they add grated Cheddar and then this lovely sauce is gently combined with gluten free rice pasta to create a dish that everyone can savour and enjoy, whether they are gluten intolerant or not.

There's no better dessert to share around. Have you earned a big slice, a small slice or the whole Viennetta? No matter how big or small the slice, eating Viennetta will make things nice. Get your hands on this delicious dessert to impress any crowd or family gathering. Streets Viennetta is also available in delicious Chocolate, so why not try both? Between World War 1 and World War 2, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted Street. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one horse power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well known brands such as Magnum, Viennetta, Paddle Pop, Cornetto, Gaytime, Calippo and Blue Ribbon.

Products.RichDescription:
The history of Pao de Queijo begins over 400 years ago in the rich farmlands of the newly discovered Brazil.

Pao de Queijo is literally translated from Portuguese as cheese bread, a snack food that was so irresistible that it quickly spread throughout the country. Brazilian everyday life has become ingrained with the legend of Pao de Queijo, ever-present at special events and gatherings.

With a history of bringing people together and lifting their spirits during lunch, dinner or whenever hunger strikes...

Pao de Queijo is something that has to be tried to be believed!

-All natural.

-Made with real cheese.
